│ `0xfffffffffffffffc`.                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ - `%gep2 = getelementptr nusw i8, ptr %y, i64 %z`: `10 + (-4)` (signed) = `6`. The `nusw` constraint holds as the offset is negative and the result is smaller than the base. So,        │
│ `%gep2` is `6`.                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ - `%cmp = icmp ult ptr %gep1, %gep2`: `icmp ult 0xfffffffffffffffc, 6` is `false`.                                                                                                       │
